Somerset Holdings | Products














































Somerset Holdings





  Products



 
Somerset arranges Treaty Reinsurance and Treaty Catastrophe Retrocession cover for a wide range of companies, insurers and reinsurers, both large and small. 

 
We take a constructive view and are considerably more creative in our approach, using both capital and traditional markets. By evaluating your specific needs, we tailor-make the most appropriate product and customize it to fit efficiently into your portfolio.
For all the following classes of business, cover can be arranged on a treaty proportional or non-proportional basis, including exposure or reciprocity arrangements (SWAPS), Industry Loss Warranty (including live and dead catastrophe), and replicat.



Agriculture/Crop
Proportional and stop loss.



Aviation
Airline, General Aviation and Speciality Aviation.​ 



Marine
Ocean and inland, including hull, yachts, cargo, liability and offshore energy.



Property
US, Europe, Japan and specific territories, Farm Mutuals and smaller Regional companies.



Weather
Temperature, Rainfall, Snowfall, Humidity, Solar Radiation, Wind Speed and weather-driven commodity businesses. 



Interested? Get in touch 












Somerset Holdings | History














































Somerset Holdings





  History



 
Founded by John Brooks, Somerset Holdings Ltd (SHL) is a Bermuda based reinsurance intermediary, regulated by the Bermuda Money Authority (BMA). 



SHL’s position as an independent intermediary domiciled in Bermuda places it on the doorstep of the most dynamic reinsurance marketplace in the world. Our relationships with intermediaries and underwriters in the key insurance markets of the UK and United States give us extensive reach and breadth.
John Brooks has over 40 years of experience in the London market, including setting up a Lloyd’s broker in 1990. The Lloyds broker originally started out handling predominately Marine Reinsurance; however, the company quickly developed into a multi-class broking house handling Property, Aviation (airline and GA) as well as Marine.
In 2003, the company was acquired by HRH, a large US broker at the time John remained a director of the company until his departure in December 2007. Somerset Holdings Ltd was formed in 2008 and approved by the BMA during late 2008.

